raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "stumpy" %}
{% set version = "1.11.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 1ba79b295c9b52a66943e2d35a15ac84e824e27d68ec9829894bdef2ed6afb2f

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.7
    - pip
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python >=3.7
    - numpy >=1.17
    - scipy >=1.5
    - numba >=0.54

test:
  requires:
    - setuptools
  imports:
    - stumpy

about:
  home: http://github.com/TDAmeritrade/stumpy
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: 'STUMPY is a powerful and scalable Python library that computes something called a matrix profile, which can then be used for a variety of time series data mining tasks'

  dev_url: https://github.com/TDAmeritrade/stumpy

    - seanlaw
